[
    {
        "content": "<p>In response to <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/module.20and.20package.20changes\">this topic</a>.</p>\n<p>For apps, instead of:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>app [main] packages [Stdout from &quot;https://…&quot;]\n\nmain =\n    Stdout.line &quot;Hello, World!&quot;\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I would prefer:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>app\n    exposes [main]\n    imports [Stdout from &quot;https://…&quot;]\n\nmain =\n    Stdout.line &quot;Hello, World!&quot;\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 372260170,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1688467419
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was going to say something similar to this, when I read the word <code>packages</code> I read it as a verb, like \"this app packages these things\" instead of the noun like \"these are the packages to import\". Maybe that's because I was used to the current Roc syntax and expected it to read like a sentence, I could probably just get used to a noun like in most languages manifest files.</p>",
        "id": 372451351,
        "sender_full_name": "Hannes",
        "timestamp": 1688525402
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure about the word <code>exposes</code> for an app, I know what you mean - that it's exposed to the platform - but I think that would be overloading the meaning of the word too much.</p>",
        "id": 372452030,
        "sender_full_name": "Hannes",
        "timestamp": 1688525862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah especially when it's on a single line, it looks like it's supposed to be read aloud as an English sentence: \"app 'main' packages standard out\". And in that sentence, \"packages\" is a verb.</p>",
        "id": 372540912,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Carroll",
        "timestamp": 1688553363
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>combining some ideas from other threads: what if it was this?</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/c09p2nfdufepJ17j3-n-MRBq/Screen-Shot-2023-07-19-at-12.01.44-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2023-07-19-at-12.01.44-AM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/c09p2nfdufepJ17j3-n-MRBq/Screen-Shot-2023-07-19-at-12.01.44-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2023-07-19-at-12.01.44-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/22008/c09p2nfdufepJ17j3-n-MRBq/Screen-Shot-2023-07-19-at-12.01.44-AM.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 376528236,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739337
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>to expand that a bit:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">main</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">imports</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Stdout</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/basic-cli/…\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">JsonDecode</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/json/…\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">CodePt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Segment</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/unicode/…\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 376528596,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739463
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so <code>from platform</code> would be what denotes which one is the platform</p>",
        "id": 376528627,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it could also have brackets around the <code>imports</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">main</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">imports</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Stdout</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/basic-cli/…\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">JsonDecode</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/json/…\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">CodePt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Segment</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/unicode/…\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 376528738,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739522
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I really don't like the first impression that <code>[[</code> makes on hello world:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>app [main] imports [[Stdout] from platform &quot;https://…/basic-cli/…&quot;]\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 376528796,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739560
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and it doesn't feel like the brackets are adding a lot of important clarity to the multiline version to me</p>",
        "id": 376528918,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689739591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we need the indents for any particular reason?</p>",
        "id": 376548581,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1689748544
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this also looks nice</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">main</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">imports</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Stdout</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/basic-cli/…\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">JsonDecode</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/json/…\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">CodePt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Segment</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"https://…/unicode/…\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"nf\">main</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 376549350,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1689748796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I prefer with the indent and without the brackets around the imports</p>",
        "id": 376640740,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1689768585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I like the indentation because it's continuing the <code>app</code> declaration as opposed to starting a new standalone declaration</p>",
        "id": 376658686,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1689771852
    }
]